{"$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#", "properties": {"bytes_limit": {"type": "integer", "description": "Limits search to specified number of bytes - default zero (no limit - match entire captured buffer)."}, "patterns": {"items": {"$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#", "properties": {"string_match": {"type": "string", "description": "Text string to be located in HTTP body."}, "binary_match": {"type": "string", "description": "Sequence of bytes to be located in HTTP body."}}, "additionalProperties": true, "type": "object"}, "type": "array", "description": "List of patterns to match."}}, "additionalProperties": true, "type": "object", "description": "HTTP generic body match configuration.\n List of text strings and hex strings to be located in HTTP body.\n All specified strings must be found in the HTTP body for positive match.\n The search may be limited to specified number of bytes from the body start.\n\n .. attention::\n\n   Searching for patterns in HTTP body is potentially cpu intensive. For each specified pattern, http body is scanned byte by byte to find a match.\n   If multiple patterns are specified, the process is repeated for each pattern. If location of a pattern is known, ``bytes_limit`` should be specified\n   to scan only part of the http body."}